.planning/phases/03-numpress-linear-mz/03-01-SUMMARY.md:84:## L2 bound measured
.planning/phases/03-numpress-linear-mz/03-01-SUMMARY.md:85:Decoded numpress m/z compared positionally to `--lossless` (Phase-2 proven bit-exact to source): per-chunk decoded length == intensity == lossless length; total compared == `spectrum_data_point_count` (305,213); both start and end anchors within 0.5/fp; **worst |Δm/z| ≈ 1.6e-7 Th** (well under the ~5e-7 worst-case bound). Intensity is **bit-exact f32** (0 mismatches) in numpress mode; `--lossless` and `--point` remain BITWISE-L1.
.planning/phases/03-numpress-linear-mz/03-01-SUMMARY.md:89:**1. [Rule 1 - Bug] int32 wraparound in numpress decode/accumulation**
.planning/phases/03-numpress-linear-mz/03-01-SUMMARY.md:91:- **Issue:** The canonical algorithm uses unsigned 32-bit `ints`; a literal uint32 port wraps `2*ints[1]-ints[0]` once m/z*fp exceeds 2^32 and then divides the wrapped value, corrupting all values past that point. pynumpress avoids this by accumulating in a wider integer before the float divide.
.planning/phases/03-numpress-linear-mz/03-01-SUMMARY.md:92:- **Fix:** Accumulate `ints` in `int64` in both EncodeLinear and DecodeLinear (the on-wire diff stays the low-32-bit `int` so byte output remains identical to pynumpress). Verified byte-identity preserved and round-trip clean to n=4000.
.planning/phases/03-numpress-linear-mz/03-01-SUMMARY.md:93:- **Files:** MSNumpress.cs. **Commit:** f1bfaa1.
.planning/phases/03-numpress-linear-mz/03-01-SUMMARY.md:97:- **Issue:** encodeInt stores the low (8-l) nibbles of the value; the first decode pass placed read nibbles at positions n..7 instead of 0..(7-n).
.planning/phases/03-numpress-linear-mz/03-01-SUMMARY.md:99:- **Files:** MSNumpress.cs. **Commit:** f1bfaa1.
.planning/phases/03-numpress-linear-mz/03-01-SUMMARY.md:101:**3. [Rule 2 - Critical] L2 anchor float slack**
.planning/phases/03-numpress-linear-mz/03-01-SUMMARY.md:103:- **Issue:** The end-anchor check (exact source m/z vs quantized decode) exceeded the strict `0.5/fp` by ~2e-15 due to round-half quantization + float division.
.planning/phases/03-numpress-linear-mz/03-01-SUMMARY.md:104:- **Fix:** Allow `(0.5/fp)*(1+1e-6)` slack on anchor checks; the independent `worstAbs <= 5e-7` global bound (with large headroom) remains strict.
.planning/phases/03-numpress-linear-mz/03-01-SUMMARY.md:107:**Deviation vs ROADMAP CURIE:** ROADMAP NP-02 says MS:1003089 for numpress; the verified reference dump shows numpress = **MS:1002312** (MS:1003089 is delta). MS:1002312 used and documented.
.planning/phases/03-numpress-linear-mz/03-01-SUMMARY.md:110:None. mz_chunk_values is intentionally NULL in numpress mode (the m/z lives in mz_numpress_linear_bytes); this is the reference layout, not a stub.
.planning/phases/03-numpress-linear-mz/03-01-SUMMARY.md:113:- MSNumpress.cs exists; commits f1bfaa1, f387d50, 47dc5ad, 8137004 present on main.
.planning/phases/03-numpress-linear-mz/03-01-SUMMARY.md:117:- The numpress branch lives inside ChunkFacetStream keyed on the numpress flag; ZRS zero-run null-marking applies to the delta (`--lossless`) m/z values path and/or intensity — numpress carries raw bytes, so ZRS would interact with the lossless/intensity columns, not the numpress bytes.
.planning/phases/03-numpress-linear-mz/03-01-SUMMARY.md:118:- `MzPeakChunkCodec.NumpressDecode` (anchor-aligned, short-chunk guarded) is the canonical reader-side helper for decoding our numpress output.
.planning/phases/03-numpress-linear-mz/03-01-SUMMARY.md:119:- Intensity-SLOF (Numpress short-logged-float) remains the deferred backlog item that would unlock the reference's ~63% headline; m/z numpress alone yields ~19% on small.RAW.
.planning/phases/03-numpress-linear-mz/03-01-SUMMARY.md:122:*Phase: 03-numpress-linear-mz*
.planning/phases/03-numpress-linear-mz/RESEARCH-schema.md:1:# Phase 3: Numpress-Linear m/z — Reference Schema + Conformance (sub-report)
.planning/phases/03-numpress-linear-mz/RESEARCH-schema.md:4:**Scope:** Schema / footer / fixed-point / validator conformance ONLY. The C# MSNumpress port is covered by a separate sub-report.
.planning/phases/03-numpress-linear-mz/RESEARCH-schema.md:5:**Method:** `python3.11` + `pyarrow 24.0.0` + `pynumpress` over `refs/mzPeak/small.numpress.mzpeak` (authoritative Rust-writer output) and `small.chunked.mzpeak` (delta baseline). `mzpeak-validate` (profile mzpeak-0.9) run on both.
.planning/phases/03-numpress-linear-mz/RESEARCH-schema.md:8:> **Provenance:** All schema/footer/CURIE/byte facts are `[VERIFIED: pyarrow dump of refs/mzPeak/small.numpress.mzpeak]`. The intrinsic m/z error bound is `[VERIFIED: pynumpress decode + 0.5/fp]`. Numpress algorithm semantics are `[CITED: ms-numpress canonical]`.
.planning/phases/03-numpress-linear-mz/RESEARCH-schema.md:12:## CRITICAL FINDING — the reference numpress mode also Numpress-encodes intensity (SLOF)
.planning/phases/03-numpress-linear-mz/RESEARCH-schema.md:14:The Phase-3 CONTEXT.md assumes "intensity stays lossless f32 / NOT numpress'd in v2." **The authoritative reference contradicts this.** `small.numpress.mzpeak` was produced with `-c numpress:50 --intensity-numpress-slof` and its chunk struct carries an **8th field `intensity_numpress_slof_bytes`** (transform `MS:1002314`, numpress short-logged-float), with the plain `intensity` list **absent entirely** (no `chunk_secondary` entry in the footer).
.planning/phases/03-numpress-linear-mz/RESEARCH-schema.md:18:- **Option A (match the reference byte-for-byte):** emit `intensity_numpress_slof_bytes` (SLOF, MS:1002314), drop the plain `intensity` list. Intensity becomes **lossy** (SLOF ~ 2-significant-digit log error). This is what drives the headline ~63% size reduction (SLOF roughly halves intensity bytes vs the f32 list).
.planning/phases/03-numpress-linear-mz/RESEARCH-schema.md:19:- **Option B (honor CONTEXT "intensity stays lossless f32"):** numpress ONLY m/z; keep the plain `intensity` list exactly as Phase-2. This is a *valid* archive (the validator does not require intensity be numpress'd) but will NOT be byte-identical to `small.numpress.mzpeak` and will be materially larger than the reference (the m/z numpress saving alone is ~50% of m/z, not 63% overall).
.planning/phases/03-numpress-linear-mz/RESEARCH-schema.md:21:**Recommendation:** flag `[ASSUMED — needs user confirmation]`. The schema-diff verification in CONTEXT ("chunk schema diff vs small.numpress.mzpeak") is only satisfiable under Option A. If the intent is true byte-parity with the reference, intensity SLOF must be in scope. See Assumptions Log A1.
.planning/phases/03-numpress-linear-mz/RESEARCH-schema.md:25:## Item 1 — Exact numpress chunk schema
.planning/phases/03-numpress-linear-mz/RESEARCH-schema.md:29:- The numpress chunk struct has **7 children** (vs Phase-2's 6): the Phase-2 six PLUS `mz_numpress_linear_bytes`, and — in the reference — an 8th `intensity_numpress_slof_bytes` **replacing** the plain `intensity` list. `[VERIFIED]`
.planning/phases/03-numpress-linear-mz/RESEARCH-schema.md:30:- `mz_numpress_linear_bytes` IS present: type **`large_list<item: uint8 not null>`** (Arrow large_list; item is `uint8` and **not null**). `[VERIFIED]`
.planning/phases/03-numpress-linear-mz/RESEARCH-schema.md:31:- `mz_chunk_values` is **still present in the schema** (column not dropped) but is **NULL on every numpress row** (488/488 null, 0 non-null, 0 empty). It is NOT absent; it is present-but-all-null. `[VERIFIED]`
.planning/phases/03-numpress-linear-mz/RESEARCH-schema.md:32:- `chunk_encoding` literal value for numpress rows = **`MS:1002312`** (a CURIE — the Numpress-linear term itself, NOT the string "numpress"). All 488 rows carry this single value. Contrast Phase-2 delta where `chunk_encoding == MS:1003089`. `[VERIFIED]`
.planning/phases/03-numpress-linear-mz/RESEARCH-schema.md:33:- The plain `intensity` list field of Phase-2 is **absent** in the reference numpress file; intensity is carried as `intensity_numpress_slof_bytes` (`large_list<uint8 not null>`, transform `MS:1002314`). `[VERIFIED]`
.planning/phases/03-numpress-linear-mz/RESEARCH-schema.md:35:### Authoritative numpress chunk schema (exact pyarrow dump)
.planning/phases/03-numpress-linear-mz/RESEARCH-schema.md:39:  spectrum_index:                 uint64
.planning/phases/03-numpress-linear-mz/RESEARCH-schema.md:42:  mz_chunk_values:                large_list<item: double>      # transform=MS:1003901, buffer_format=chunk_values; ALL NULL in numpress mode
.planning/phases/03-numpress-linear-mz/RESEARCH-schema.md:43:  chunk_encoding:                 string        # transform=MS:1003901, buffer_format=chunk_encoding; value = "MS:1002312"
.planning/phases/03-numpress-linear-mz/RESEARCH-schema.md:44:  mz_numpress_linear_bytes:       large_list<item: uint8 not null>   # transform=MS:1002312, buffer_format=chunk_transform, sorting_rank=0
.planning/phases/03-numpress-linear-mz/RESEARCH-schema.md:45:  intensity_numpress_slof_bytes:  large_list<item: uint8 not null>   # transform=MS:1002314, buffer_format=chunk_transform, sorting_rank=null  [reference; Option A only]
