.planning/phases/03-numpress-linear-mz/RESEARCH-port.md:367:- **Pynumpress:** Guarantees reversibility; decode(encode(x)) ≈ x within 0.002 ppm.
.planning/phases/03-numpress-linear-mz/RESEARCH-port.md:370:**L∞ error bound:** ~2e−5 per value (empirically validated by pynumpress test suite).
.planning/phases/03-numpress-linear-mz/RESEARCH-port.md:389:- **Hand-port from C++:** The ms-numpress C++ source is ~400 lines, well-commented, and published. Porting ~150 lines of the core encode/decode logic to C# is straightforward and introduces no external runtime dependency.
.planning/phases/03-numpress-linear-mz/RESEARCH-port.md:390:- **Avoid NuGet:** No official C# NuGet package exists. A hypothetical numpress-rs via FFI would add complexity (P/Invoke, native library management).
