   320	<threat_model>
   321	## Trust Boundaries
   322	
   323	| Boundary | Description |
   324	|----------|-------------|
   325	| RAW scan data → numpress encoder | Untrusted/variable m/z arrays (empty, single-point, near-equal, non-monotone) cross into the codec |
   326	| vendored ms-numpress source → assembly | Third-party algorithm ported into our managed assembly |
   327	| numpress bytes → archive consumers | Lossy m/z bytes must be self-describing (transform CURIE) for downstream readers |
   328	
   329	## STRIDE Threat Register
   330	
   331	| Threat ID | Category | Component | Disposition | Mitigation Plan |
   332	|-----------|----------|-----------|-------------|-----------------|
   333	| T-03-01 | Tampering | Numpress encode/decode correctness | mitigate | Faithful line-for-line canonical port + exact vectors V1-V4 (OptimalLinearFixedPoint([1,2,3])==1073741823, reference row-0 fp==10599266.0, byte-identity vs ms-numpress test vector AND vs pynumpress encode) + per-chunk anti-vacuity L2 bound assertion (Tasks 1,4) |
   334	| T-03-02 | Tampering | x64 dependency reintroduction | mitigate | Pure-managed AnyCPU port (System only); explicit AnyCPU/MSIL assembly assertion in tests (Task 1) |
   335	| T-03-03 | Information disclosure | Self-describing transform | mitigate | MS:1002312 recorded in array_index footer + cv_list + data_processing lossy note (Task 2) |
   336	| T-03-04 | Denial of service | Pathological m/z slices (empty/single/2/near-equal) | mitigate | Codec edge-case tests; encoder must terminate on all slice lengths; short-chunk guards in decode (Tasks 1,2) |
   337	| T-03-05 | Repudiation | --lossless/--point silently lossy | accept→mitigate | Bitwise-L1 locks keep both modes exact; CLI warning only in numpress mode (Tasks 3,4) |
   338	| T-03-SC | Tampering | npm/pip/cargo installs | n/a | No package-manager installs introduced; ms-numpress is vendored source, not a package; python3.11/pynumpress used only as a test oracle (pre-existing on system) |
   339	</threat_model>
   340	
