   351	<success_criteria>
   352	- NP-01: pure-managed AnyCPU C# MSNumpress-linear encode+decode, faithful canonical port, no x64 dep, native arm64. ✓ Task 1
   353	- NP-02: m/z in mz_numpress_linear_bytes with chunk_encoding/transform MS:1002312, mz_chunk_values NULL (not empty), recorded in array_index AND data_processing. ✓ Task 2
   354	  (Deviation noted vs ROADMAP "MS:1003089": the verified reference dump shows numpress = MS:1002312; MS:1003089 is delta. We use MS:1002312.)
   355	- NP-03: numpress ON by default; --no-numpress/--lossless -> delta chunks; lossy note in data_processing + CLI warning; --point -> v1. ✓ Task 3
   356	- NP-04: decoded m/z within Numpress-linear bound (0.5/fp) vs source; intensity stays lossless f32. ✓ Tasks 2,4
   357	- Must NOT regress: validator 0/0 all three modes; --lossless/--point bitwise-L1; streaming per-chunk encode preserved. ✓ Task 4
   358	- Scope lock honored: intensity is plain f32 (no SLOF); intensity-SLOF deferred to backlog.
   359	</success_criteria>
   360	
   361	<risks>
   362	- **Numpress port correctness / L2 bound (chief):** the encodeInt 4-bit half-byte residual scheme and the 4-byte LE int32 first-value packing are the easiest places to mis-port — and the RESEARCH-port.md PROSE actively misleads (it claims least-squares slope + 5-byte values / continuation-varint nibbles, all wrong). The executor MUST port from the canonical reference source, not the prose. Mitigated by the exact vectors: OptimalLinearFixedPoint([1,2,3])==1073741823, reference row-0 fp==10599266.0, and BYTE-IDENTITY vs both the ms-numpress test vector and pynumpress encode at a shared fp (not merely decode-within-bound), plus the per-chunk anti-vacuity 0.5/fp decode assertion. The phantom-leading-value decode artifact is handled in the codec's anchor-aligned decode helper (with short-chunk guards), not the raw codec.
   363	- **Reintroducing an x64 dependency:** port uses System only; AnyCPU/MSIL assembly assertion guards against an accidental native pull-in.
   364	- **Keeping --lossless/--point bit-exact:** numpress is gated behind a flag and a separate struct/footer; the delta path and point path are untouched, and bitwise-L1 locks fail loudly if either regresses.
   365	- **CURIE discrepancy:** ROADMAP says MS:1003089 for numpress; verified dump says MS:1002312. We follow the verified artifact and document the override.
   366	- **Size win is m/z-only:** without intensity SLOF the reduction is the m/z saving (not the reference's ~63%). The size lock asserts numpress < delta-chunked (the achievable target), not the reference's headline.
   367	- **Vacuous L2 pass:** a bad decode or silent drop could compare fewer/zero values and trivially pass a naive bound. Mitigated by the Task-4 anti-vacuity guards (chunk count > 0, per-chunk + total length parity vs spectrum_data_point_count, both start/end anchors, short-chunk guards).
   368	</risks>
   369	
