    12	## CRITICAL FINDING — the reference numpress mode also Numpress-encodes intensity (SLOF)
    13	
    14	The Phase-3 CONTEXT.md assumes "intensity stays lossless f32 / NOT numpress'd in v2." **The authoritative reference contradicts this.** `small.numpress.mzpeak` was produced with `-c numpress:50 --intensity-numpress-slof` and its chunk struct carries an **8th field `intensity_numpress_slof_bytes`** (transform `MS:1002314`, numpress short-logged-float), with the plain `intensity` list **absent entirely** (no `chunk_secondary` entry in the footer).
    15	
    16	This is a scope decision for the planner/discuss-phase, not a settled fact to implement blindly:
    17	
    18	- **Option A (match the reference byte-for-byte):** emit `intensity_numpress_slof_bytes` (SLOF, MS:1002314), drop the plain `intensity` list. Intensity becomes **lossy** (SLOF ~ 2-significant-digit log error). This is what drives the headline ~63% size reduction (SLOF roughly halves intensity bytes vs the f32 list).
    19	- **Option B (honor CONTEXT "intensity stays lossless f32"):** numpress ONLY m/z; keep the plain `intensity` list exactly as Phase-2. This is a *valid* archive (the validator does not require intensity be numpress'd) but will NOT be byte-identical to `small.numpress.mzpeak` and will be materially larger than the reference (the m/z numpress saving alone is ~50% of m/z, not 63% overall).
    20	
    21	**Recommendation:** flag `[ASSUMED — needs user confirmation]`. The schema-diff verification in CONTEXT ("chunk schema diff vs small.numpress.mzpeak") is only satisfiable under Option A. If the intent is true byte-parity with the reference, intensity SLOF must be in scope. See Assumptions Log A1.
    22	
    23	---
    24	
    25	## Item 1 — Exact numpress chunk schema
    26	
    27	### Decisions
    28	
    29	- The numpress chunk struct has **7 children** (vs Phase-2's 6): the Phase-2 six PLUS `mz_numpress_linear_bytes`, and — in the reference — an 8th `intensity_numpress_slof_bytes` **replacing** the plain `intensity` list. `[VERIFIED]`
    30	- `mz_numpress_linear_bytes` IS present: type **`large_list<item: uint8 not null>`** (Arrow large_list; item is `uint8` and **not null**). `[VERIFIED]`
    31	- `mz_chunk_values` is **still present in the schema** (column not dropped) but is **NULL on every numpress row** (488/488 null, 0 non-null, 0 empty). It is NOT absent; it is present-but-all-null. `[VERIFIED]`
    32	- `chunk_encoding` literal value for numpress rows = **`MS:1002312`** (a CURIE — the Numpress-linear term itself, NOT the string "numpress"). All 488 rows carry this single value. Contrast Phase-2 delta where `chunk_encoding == MS:1003089`. `[VERIFIED]`
    33	- The plain `intensity` list field of Phase-2 is **absent** in the reference numpress file; intensity is carried as `intensity_numpress_slof_bytes` (`large_list<uint8 not null>`, transform `MS:1002314`). `[VERIFIED]`
    34	
    35	### Authoritative numpress chunk schema (exact pyarrow dump)
    36	
    37	```
    38	chunk: struct<
    39	  spectrum_index:                 uint64
    40	  mz_chunk_start:                 double        # transform=MS:1003901, buffer_format=chunk_start, sorting_rank=0
    41	  mz_chunk_end:                   double        # transform=MS:1003901, buffer_format=chunk_end,   sorting_rank=0
    42	  mz_chunk_values:                large_list<item: double>      # transform=MS:1003901, buffer_format=chunk_values; ALL NULL in numpress mode
    43	  chunk_encoding:                 string        # transform=MS:1003901, buffer_format=chunk_encoding; value = "MS:1002312"
    44	  mz_numpress_linear_bytes:       large_list<item: uint8 not null>   # transform=MS:1002312, buffer_format=chunk_transform, sorting_rank=0
    45	  intensity_numpress_slof_bytes:  large_list<item: uint8 not null>   # transform=MS:1002314, buffer_format=chunk_transform, sorting_rank=null  [reference; Option A only]
    46	>
    47	```
    48	
    49	Per-child Arrow field metadata (kv pairs attached to each leaf, verbatim from the file):
    50	
    51	| child | Arrow type | array_accession | data_type_accession | buffer_format | transform | sorting_rank | unit |
    52	|-------|-----------|-----------------|---------------------|---------------|-----------|--------------|------|
    53	| spectrum_index | uint64 | — | — | — | — | — | — |
    54	| mz_chunk_start | double | MS:1000514 | MS:1000523 | chunk_start | MS:1003901 | 0 | MS:1000040 |
    55	| mz_chunk_end | double | MS:1000514 | MS:1000523 | chunk_end | MS:1003901 | 0 | MS:1000040 |
    56	| mz_chunk_values | large_list\<double\> | MS:1000514 | MS:1000523 | chunk_values | MS:1003901 | 0 | MS:1000040 |
    57	| chunk_encoding | string | MS:1000514 | MS:1000523 | chunk_encoding | MS:1003901 | 0 | MS:1000040 |
    58	| mz_numpress_linear_bytes | large_list\<uint8 not null\> | MS:1000514 | MS:1000523 | chunk_transform | **MS:1002312** | 0 | MS:1000040 |
    59	| intensity_numpress_slof_bytes | large_list\<uint8 not null\> | MS:1000515 | MS:1000521 | chunk_transform | **MS:1002314** | null | MS:1000131 |
    60	
    61	### Representative rows (spectrum 0, first 3 chunk rows)
    62	
    63	| row | spectrum_index | mz_chunk_start | mz_chunk_end | mz_chunk_values | chunk_encoding | mz_numpress_linear_bytes | intensity_numpress_slof_bytes |
    64	|-----|---------------|----------------|--------------|-----------------|----------------|--------------------------|-------------------------------|
    65	| 0 | 0 | 202.60657 | 252.42885 | **None** | MS:1002312 | len=838, `[65,100,55,108,64,0,0,0,...]` | len=1560, `[64,184,23,0,...]` |
    66	| 1 | 0 | 252.96545 | 296.15249 | **None** | MS:1002312 | len=787 | len=1520 |
    67	| 2 | 0 | 307.15215 | 349.60400 | **None** | MS:1002312 | len=399 | len=670 |
    68	
    69	- First 8 bytes of each numpress block = the **fixed point as a big-endian IEEE-754 double** (row0 = `10599266.0`). This is the standard MSNumpress prefix layout.
    70	- `mz_chunk_start`/`mz_chunk_end` are the true first/last m/z of the chunk (kept as plain f64 anchors even though the values themselves are inside the numpress bytes). They still carry transform `MS:1003901` and `sorting_rank:0` — i.e. numpress mode does NOT change the anchor columns' metadata, only adds the bytes column and nulls `mz_chunk_values`.
    71	
    72	### EXACTLY how numpress differs from the Phase-2 delta schema
    73	
    74	| aspect | Phase-2 delta (`MzPeakSpectrumWriter.ChunkStructField`) | Numpress (reference) |
    75	|--------|--------------------------------------------------------|----------------------|
    76	| `chunk_encoding` value | `MS:1003089` | **`MS:1002312`** |
    77	| `mz_chunk_values` | populated (delta list) | present-but-**NULL** (every row) |
    78	| `mz_numpress_linear_bytes` | **field absent** | present, `large_list<uint8 not null>`, populated |
    79	| intensity carrier | plain `intensity` list `large_list<float>` (transform MS:1003902, buffer_format chunk_secondary) | **`intensity_numpress_slof_bytes`** `large_list<uint8 not null>` (transform MS:1002314, buffer_format chunk_transform); plain `intensity` list **absent** *(Option A)* |
    80	| struct field count | 6 | 7 (m/z-only / Option B) or 8 (reference / Option A) |
    81	
    82	**Phase-2 SUMMARY note that needs correcting:** the SUMMARY says "Numpress-linear = its own CURIE" and "in delta mode the column is ABSENT (verified: `ChunkingStrategy::Delta::extra_arrays() -> vec![]`)" — both confirmed. But it also assumed only ONE extra array (mz). The reference adds **two** extra arrays (mz linear + intensity slof) because the reference was built with intensity SLOF on.
    83	
    84	---
    85	
    86	## Item 2 — Transform / array_index recording
    87	
    88	### Decisions
    89	
    90	- The numpress transform is recorded in **two places only**: (1) the Arrow column metadata on each chunk leaf, and (2) the `spectrum_array_index` footer JSON. It is **NOT** recorded as a CURIE in `data_processing_method_list` — the reference records only a free-text "conversion options" string there. `[VERIFIED]`
    91	- Literal Numpress-linear transform CURIE = **`MS:1002312`** (confirmed against the file: it is both the `chunk_encoding` column value AND the `transform` on the `mz_numpress_linear_bytes` entry). `[VERIFIED]`
    92	- Literal Numpress-SLOF (intensity) transform CURIE = **`MS:1002314`**. `[VERIFIED]`
    93	- The m/z anchor columns (`chunk_start`/`chunk_end`/`chunk_values`/`chunk_encoding`) keep transform **`MS:1003901`** — same as the delta file. Only the new bytes columns use `MS:1002312`/`MS:1002314`. `[VERIFIED]`
    94	- `buffer_format` for both numpress-bytes entries = **`chunk_transform`** (a new buffer_format vs Phase-2's `chunk_values`/`chunk_secondary`; it is in the validator's allowed enum). `[VERIFIED]`
    95	
    96	### Exact `spectrum_array_index` footer JSON our writer must emit (numpress, reference / Option A)
    97	
    98	The footer has **6 entries** (4 m/z anchor entries with MS:1003901, then the numpress m/z bytes entry, then the numpress intensity bytes entry). Verbatim from the file:
    99	
   100	```json
   101	{
   102	  "prefix": "chunk",
   103	  "entries": [
   104	    {"context":"spectrum","path":"chunk.mz_chunk_start","data_type":"MS:1000523","array_type":"MS:1000514",
   105	     "array_name":"m/z array","unit":"MS:1000040","buffer_format":"chunk_start","transform":"MS:1003901",
   106	     "data_processing_id":null,"buffer_priority":"primary","sorting_rank":0},
   107	    {"context":"spectrum","path":"chunk.mz_chunk_end","data_type":"MS:1000523","array_type":"MS:1000514",
   108	     "array_name":"m/z array","unit":"MS:1000040","buffer_format":"chunk_end","transform":"MS:1003901",
   109	     "data_processing_id":null,"buffer_priority":"primary","sorting_rank":0},
   110	    {"context":"spectrum","path":"chunk.mz_chunk_values","data_type":"MS:1000523","array_type":"MS:1000514",
   111	     "array_name":"m/z array","unit":"MS:1000040","buffer_format":"chunk_values","transform":"MS:1003901",
   112	     "data_processing_id":null,"buffer_priority":"primary","sorting_rank":0},
   113	    {"context":"spectrum","path":"chunk.chunk_encoding","data_type":"MS:1000523","array_type":"MS:1000514",
   114	     "array_name":"m/z array","unit":"MS:1000040","buffer_format":"chunk_encoding","transform":"MS:1003901",
   115	     "data_processing_id":null,"buffer_priority":"primary","sorting_rank":0},
   116	    {"context":"spectrum","path":"chunk.mz_numpress_linear_bytes","data_type":"MS:1000523","array_type":"MS:1000514",
   117	     "array_name":"m/z array","unit":"MS:1000040","buffer_format":"chunk_transform","transform":"MS:1002312",
   118	     "data_processing_id":null,"buffer_priority":"primary","sorting_rank":0},
   119	    {"context":"spectrum","path":"chunk.intensity_numpress_slof_bytes","data_type":"MS:1000521","array_type":"MS:1000515",
   120	     "array_name":"intensity array","unit":"MS:1000131","buffer_format":"chunk_transform","transform":"MS:1002314",
   121	     "data_processing_id":null,"buffer_priority":"primary","sorting_rank":null}
   122	  ]
