   343	
   344	## 7. Determinism & Parity with Reference
   345	
   346	### 7.1 Fixed-Point Determination
   347	
   348	The `optimalLinearFixedPoint` function implements a **deterministic least-squares fit**. Given the same input array, it should produce the same fixed point as:
   349	- pynumpress (Python reference)
   350	- numpress-rs (Rust reference)
   351	
   352	**Why deterministic:**
   353	- Linear algebra: least-squares solution is unique (assuming full rank, which it is for typical m/z).
   354	- No randomization: the algorithm is purely algebraic.
   355	
   356	### 7.2 Byte Identity
   357	
   358	Once the fixed point is determined, the encoding is **byte-deterministic**:
   359	- 5-byte ints are packed identically.
   360	- 4-bit half-bytes are packed identically.

